    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Psalms",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 48,
        "summary": "Zion, the city of God, the joy of the whole earth, will be established forever.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Great is the Lord, and greatly to be praised in the city of our God, in the mountain of his holiness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0His holy mountain.",
                        "start": 72,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 2:3 (2\u20135).",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 84
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 2:6.",
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 100
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 6,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Beautiful for situation, the joy of the whole earth, is mount Zion, on the sides of the north, the city of the great King.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Beauty.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lam. 2:15; Ezek. 20:6.",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Zion.",
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 66
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "There was in various lands a concept that the dwelling place of Deity was in the \u201cnorth.\u201d Isa. 14:13.",
                        "start": 88,
                        "end": 93
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 5:35.",
                        "start": 99,
                        "end": 103
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 55
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "God is known in her palaces for a refuge.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For, lo, the kings were assembled, they passed by together.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They saw it, and so they marvelled; they were troubled, and hasted away.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 59
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Fear took hold upon them there, and pain, as of a woman in travail.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Woman.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou breakest the ships of Tarshish with an east wind.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 2:16; Ezek. 27:25.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As we have heard, so have we seen in the city of the Lord of hosts, in the city of our God: God will establish it for ever. Selah.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "We have thought of thy lovingkindness, O God, in the midst of thy temple.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "According to thy name, O God, so is thy praise unto the ends of the earth: thy right hand is full of righteousness.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:58.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 21
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Let mount Zion rejoice, let the daughters of Judah be glad, because of thy judgments.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 97:8.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Walk about Zion, and go round about her: tell the towers thereof.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Mark ye well her bulwarks, consider her palaces; that ye may tell it to the generation following.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 102:18.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 86
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For this God is our God for ever and ever: he will be our guide even unto death.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 20:12; Abr. 1:19.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}